creator: Henry Kendall
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 11 recordings of God Help Our Men at Sea by Henry Kendall. This was the Weekly Poetry project for July 19, 2015. Read in English by Algy Pug; Bruce Kachuk; David Lawrence; Newgatenovelist; Greg Giordano; VoiceOfJosh; Larry Wilson; Leonard Wilson; Maria Kasper; NoelBadrian and Rosslyn Carlyle. Kendall was born in a settler's hut by Yackungarrah Creek near Ulladulla, New South Wales, Australia. He was registered as Thomas Henry Kendall, but never appears to have used his first name. His three volumes of verse were all published under the name of "Henry Kendall". ( Wikipedia ) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (14MB)
